        <h1>Travel advice for multiple events on 4 September</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        01 September 2005
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        On Sunday, 4th September the following events will be occurring within central London:
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<ul>
<li><a href="/static/corporate/media/newscentre/archive/4092.html">Tour of Britain Cycle Race</a> (1000-1800)<br>World class professional cycling race around a one mile circuit starting and finishing in Whitehall, following a route through Trafalgar Square, Northumberland Avenue, Victoria Embankment and Parliament Square. </li>
<li><strong>Regent Street Festival</strong> (1200-2000)<br>An international festival featuring food, music, shopping and activities. </li>
<li><strong>Hydro active Women's Challenge</strong> (1000-1300)<br>A "women only" 5km run/walk marathon through Hyde Park to raise money for Great Ormond Street Hospital Children's Charity and various other charities.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Travel advice on the day:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Tube:</strong></p>
<p>The following stations will be very busy as a result: <br>Bayswater, High Street Kensington, Hyde Park Corner, Knightsbridge, Lancaster Gate, Marble Arch, Notting Hill Gate, Queensway, Charing Cross, Embankment, Green Park, Oxford Circus, Westminster, Piccadilly Circus and Leicester Square.</p>
<p>For those who wish, bicycles can be taken free of charge on some sections of the Underground.</p>
<ul>
<li>Outside of peak times bicycles are allowed:<br>On all sections of the Circle, District, East London, Hammersmith &amp; City and Metropolitan lines </li>
<li>Between Queen's Park - Harrow &amp; Wealdstone on the Bakerloo line </li>
<li>Between Finchley Road - Stanmore and Canning Town - Stratford on the Jubilee line. </li>
<li>Between Edgware - Colindale, Hendon Central - Golders Green and East Finchley - High Barnet/Mill Hill East on the Northern line. </li>
<li>Between Barons Court - Hounslow West/Uxbridge and Cockfosters - Oakwood on the Piccadilly line. </li>
<li>Between West Ruislip/Ealing Broadway - White City, Leyton - Epping, Newbury Park/Woodford - Hainault on the Central line</li></ul>
<p>Bicycles are not allowed on:</p>
<ul>
<li>Victoria line </li>
<li>Waterloo &amp; City line </li>
<li>DLR and Croydon Tramlink</li></ul>
<p><strong>Tube network disruption</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>District line - due to track replacement work at Barons Court no trains between Earl's Court and Richmond/Acton Town. Reduced services throughout the reminder of the line, except Edgware Road - Olympia. Two Replacement Services will operate. </li>
<li>Piccadilly line -due to track replacement work - no trains between Hyde Park Corner to Acton Town </li>
<li>Bakerloo line - due to track replacement work no trains between Stonebridge Park to Harrow &amp; Wealdstone</li></ul>
<p><strong>Buses</strong>:</p>
<p>Due to the Tour of Britain and the Regent Street Festival, significant bus curtailments and diversions will be in effect in the area.</p>
<p>The following routes are affected:</p>
<p>3, 6, 9, 11, 12, 13, 15, 23, 24, 29, 53, 77A, 88, 91, 94, 139, 148, 159, 176, 211, 453, C2, N2, N3, N11, N13, N15, N16, N18, N23, N36, N44, N52, N77, N155, N159, N279, N343, N381.</p>
<p><strong>Road closures:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Whitehall and Parliament Street (both directions) 0500 - 2030 </li>
<li>Bridge Street (both directions) 0700 - 1700 </li>
<li>Victoria Embankment from Bridge Street - Northumberland Avenue (both directions) 0700 - 1700 </li>
<li>Northumberland Avenue (both directions) 0700 - 1700 </li>
<li>Regent Street between Piccadilly Circus and Oxford Circus will be closed to traffic from 0400 Sunday until 0200 Monday 5th September.</li></ul>
<hr>
For 24-hour information on all London travel, call: 020 7222 1234 
